TI  == palindromic haemophilus dna uptake sequences in presumed transcriptional terminators from h. influenzae and h. parainfluenzae.
AB  == we have found palindromic pairs of near matches to the 11-bp haemophilus dna uptake motif shortly after the stop codons of three haemophilus genes. short runs of thymidylate residues follow the stem-loop structures thus defined. this organization suggests that, in h. influenzae, the uptake motif may be preferentially incorporated into gene termination signals, as has been proposed for neisseria gonorrhoeae.
