TI  == neonatal infections with haemophilus species.
AB  == during a 27 month study seven nonserotypable strains of haemophilus influenzae and two of haemophilus parainfluenzae were isolated from nine neonates. seven had early infection associated with respiratory distress or conjunctivitis; three had septicaemia one of whom died. the incidence of haemophilus septicaemia was 0.23 per 1000 live births.
