PMID== 6341938
TI  == [haemophilus influenzae and parainfluenzae in children. a retrospective study of  52 cases].
AB  == fifty-two children hospitalized in the pediatric service of a general hospital between january 1978 and december 1979 were found to be infected with haemophilus influenzae or para-influenzae (43 with h. influenzae and 9 with para-influenzae). most of these children (34/52) were less than 4 years of age. the localizations of infections were as follow: 5 meningitis with satisfactory resolution except for 1 who developed slight deafness, 1 epiglotitis, 11 pneumonias or bronchopneumonias, 1 arthritis, 10 otitis medias, 6 conjunctivitis, 3 sinusitis,  10 upper airway infections and 1 neonatal infection. on 8 of these cases the patients were felt to be carriers of h. influenzae or para-influenzae, the signs  and symptoms beeing not related to these bacteria. these results are compared with those found in the literature.
