PMID== 303852
TI  == [the occurrence of neuraminidase and n-acetylneuraminate-pyruvate lyase in pathogenic haemophili of man (author's transl)].
AB  == we investigated the following six haemophilus species from man for the both enzymes neuraminidase and n-acetylneuraminate pyruvate lyase: h. aegypticus, h. aphrophilus, h. influenzae. h. parahaemolyticus, h. parainfluenzae and h. vaginalis. it is shown that h. vaginalis does not produce either neuraminidase or n-acetylneuraminate pyruvate lyase. he differs, therefore, from all other investigated haemophili producing both enzymes, neuraminidase and n-acetylneuraminate pyruvate lyase. colominic acid, na-salt, is splitted better than n-acetylneuraminyllactose. it can be concluded, therefore, some substrate specificity of the neuramindase of haemophili in the sense that the alpha, 2 leads to 8 linkage of neuraminic acid is cleaved quicker than the alpha, 2 leads  to 3 linkage. the physiological and pathologenic role of the both enzymes is discussed.
